1
00:00:19,800 --> 00:00:24,980
THE GOOD BAD MOTHER

2
00:00:27,150 --> 00:00:29,310
-Goodbye, piggies.
-Goodness.

3
00:00:30,360 --> 00:00:33,320
You still feel sad every time
you send them away, don't you?

4
00:00:33,400 --> 00:00:34,990
Of course, I do.

5
00:00:35,070 --> 00:00:37,860
I lived with them and fed them
longer than my husband and kid.

6
00:00:39,950 --> 00:00:41,740
Goodbye.

7
00:00:41,830 --> 00:00:44,700
I'll take good care of your piglets.

8
00:00:44,790 --> 00:00:46,250
Don't worry about a thing.

9
00:00:46,790 --> 00:00:48,330
I'll get going then.

10
00:00:48,420 --> 00:00:49,330
-One second.
-Yes?

11
00:00:52,210 --> 00:00:55,090
These potatoes are plump and delicious.
Eat them with your kids.

12
00:00:55,170 --> 00:00:57,680
Goodness, you're always so kind.

13
00:00:58,550 --> 00:01:01,720
By the way, how's your son doing?

14
00:01:17,070 --> 00:01:18,990
-Ready or not!
-Ready or not!

15
00:01:19,070 --> 00:01:21,070
-Rock, paper, scissors, shoot!
-Rock, paper, scissors, shoot!

16
00:01:21,160 --> 00:01:22,700
-Shoot!
-Shoot!

17
00:01:23,910 --> 00:01:26,830
All right! I won!

18
00:01:27,960 --> 00:01:29,080
Okay!

19
00:01:36,010 --> 00:01:38,220
Here we go!

20
00:01:43,050 --> 00:01:46,770
Mom!

21
00:01:50,230 --> 00:01:52,560
THE GOOD BAD MOTHER

22
00:01:55,860 --> 00:01:56,990
Are you done?

23
00:01:57,070 --> 00:01:59,610
Yes, it's good as new.

24
00:01:59,700 --> 00:02:01,360
-Goodness.
-It's perfect.

25
00:02:01,450 --> 00:02:04,950
My gosh, you're such a crafty handyman.

26
00:02:05,030 --> 00:02:08,540
Your family is skilled with your hands.

27
00:02:09,250 --> 00:02:10,330
You know,

28
00:02:10,420 --> 00:02:14,540
I'm feeling sort of offended to hear that.

29
00:02:14,630 --> 00:02:17,510
Is it because I have a delinquent son?

30
00:02:17,590 --> 00:02:20,380
Don't take things that far.

31
00:02:20,470 --> 00:02:24,140
Anyway, I'm relieved that nobody got hurt.

32
00:02:24,220 --> 00:02:26,600
-Yes.
-This could've been much worse.

33
00:02:26,680 --> 00:02:28,220
Push me.

34
00:02:28,310 --> 00:02:30,390
-Here I go.
-It's smooth.

35
00:02:30,480 --> 00:02:31,980
-This is nice.
-Yes.

36
00:02:33,650 --> 00:02:36,440
They said you'd love it

37
00:02:37,360 --> 00:02:38,400
if I exercised.

38
00:02:38,480 --> 00:02:39,570
Who did?

39
00:02:41,740 --> 00:02:42,820
Goodness.

40
00:02:42,910 --> 00:02:47,910
Goodness, Mommy's little boy
wanted to make her happy.

41
00:02:47,990 --> 00:02:50,200
What a wonderful son.

42
00:02:50,290 --> 00:02:53,080
Of course, he is.

43
00:02:53,170 --> 00:02:56,750
And those clever twins
went after his weakness.

44
00:02:56,840 --> 00:02:58,170
Kids.

45
00:02:58,760 --> 00:03:01,260
How many times do I have to tell you
this is dangerous?

46
00:03:01,840 --> 00:03:05,510
That's not a toy. That's his legs.

47
00:03:05,600 --> 00:03:07,850
That's not my legs. It's a wheelchair.

48
00:03:09,520 --> 00:03:13,650
Anyway, don't ever play
around with it again, okay?

49
00:03:14,230 --> 00:03:17,940
It's not for muddy roads, icy roads,
bumpy stony paths, waterways,

50
00:03:18,020 --> 00:03:19,440
rice paddy ridges, banks,

51
00:03:19,530 --> 00:03:21,530
and especially anywhere up high.

52
00:03:21,610 --> 00:03:22,740
Okay?

53
00:03:22,820 --> 00:03:24,530
And it's not for
three people to ride, right?

54
00:03:24,610 --> 00:03:25,820
Of course not!

55
00:03:25,910 --> 00:03:26,910
See?

56
00:03:28,830 --> 00:03:32,000
What about using the rubber
tube as a hula hoop?

57
00:03:32,580 --> 00:03:33,460
What?

58
00:03:33,540 --> 00:03:34,500
Kang-ho.

59
00:03:34,580 --> 00:03:36,250
Goodness, Kang-ho…

60
00:03:36,330 --> 00:03:37,540
Goodness. Hey!

61
00:03:37,630 --> 00:03:39,210
You darned…

62
00:03:39,300 --> 00:03:40,670
little twins!

63
00:03:41,170 --> 00:03:42,340
You rascals!

64
00:03:42,420 --> 00:03:43,590
-Goodness.
-Stop.

65
00:03:43,680 --> 00:03:44,840
Don't do that.

66
00:03:44,930 --> 00:03:46,140
I already talked to them.

67
00:03:46,220 --> 00:03:50,060
Why did you drag him out and bully him?

68
00:03:50,140 --> 00:03:51,600
We didn't bully him!

69
00:03:51,680 --> 00:03:53,810
We helped him exercise!

70
00:03:53,890 --> 00:03:55,650
How are you going to help him do that?

71
00:03:56,520 --> 00:03:58,110
Look at him!

72
00:03:58,190 --> 00:04:01,230
And you can't treat him like that!

73
00:04:01,320 --> 00:04:02,610
He's not your friend!

74
00:04:02,690 --> 00:04:04,700
What? We weren't friends?

75
00:04:04,780 --> 00:04:05,950
I thought we were friends.

76
00:04:06,030 --> 00:04:07,280
You said you were seven!

77
00:04:07,370 --> 00:04:08,450
I am!

78
00:04:08,530 --> 00:04:10,160
The doctor said I'm seven!

79
00:04:10,240 --> 00:04:11,410
Right, Mom?

80
00:04:32,560 --> 00:04:34,390
Beans will grow from your tummy.

81
00:05:02,710 --> 00:05:03,880
Thirty-five.

82
00:05:04,420 --> 00:05:05,260
Repeat after me.

83
00:05:05,840 --> 00:05:06,800
Thirty-five.

84
00:05:06,880 --> 00:05:07,840
That's right.

85
00:05:08,550 --> 00:05:11,180
Kang-ho, you're 35 years old.

86
00:05:12,600 --> 00:05:15,350
But you became a little ill.

87
00:05:15,980 --> 00:05:19,730
So you became seven for a short while.

88
00:05:21,310 --> 00:05:22,570
I know what that means.

89
00:05:22,650 --> 00:05:23,570
What?

90
00:05:24,190 --> 00:05:25,400
I'm stupid, right?

91
00:05:26,820 --> 00:05:29,490
No! Who said that?

92
00:05:29,570 --> 00:05:31,240
-Who said that to you?
-You did!

93
00:05:32,330 --> 00:05:33,200
What?

94
00:05:33,280 --> 00:05:35,750
You and the doctor said that.

95
00:05:35,830 --> 00:05:37,250
"Simply put, he is…

96
00:05:37,330 --> 00:05:39,080
Simply put, he is…

97
00:05:39,170 --> 00:05:40,330
Stupid?

98
00:05:40,420 --> 00:05:41,710
…stupid."

99
00:05:49,180 --> 00:05:50,470
No, Kang-ho.

100
00:05:51,220 --> 00:05:53,640
I said that
because I didn't know any better.

101
00:05:54,510 --> 00:05:55,770
So here's the thing.

102
00:05:56,390 --> 00:05:57,350
Yes.

103
00:05:58,390 --> 00:05:59,810
Kang-ho,

104
00:05:59,890 --> 00:06:01,940
you went back to your childhood.

105
00:06:03,150 --> 00:06:06,440
Everyone wants to be young again.

106
00:06:07,110 --> 00:06:09,860
I do too. I want to go back too.

107
00:06:10,780 --> 00:06:13,660
Because if I could,
I'd be able to change many things.

108
00:06:14,830 --> 00:06:19,210
But nobody in this world
can turn back time.

109
00:06:20,580 --> 00:06:22,380
Yet you did, Kang-ho.

110
00:06:23,420 --> 00:06:24,460
This is

111
00:06:25,290 --> 00:06:26,800
a chance given from above.

112
00:06:28,050 --> 00:06:30,380
A chance to start all over again.

113
00:06:32,590 --> 00:06:34,640
"A chance given from above"?

114
00:06:35,390 --> 00:06:38,180
Yes, that's right.

115
00:06:41,640 --> 00:06:43,810
So you should be happy.

116
00:06:44,520 --> 00:06:46,940
Don't be sad or devastated.

117
00:06:47,940 --> 00:06:49,030
Be happy.

118
00:06:49,940 --> 00:06:51,740
-Happy?
-Yes.

119
00:06:52,740 --> 00:06:53,820
Your return

120
00:06:54,950 --> 00:06:56,780
makes me feel…

121
00:06:59,750 --> 00:07:01,040
happy.

122
00:07:04,500 --> 00:07:05,630
Happy.

123
00:07:11,260 --> 00:07:12,300
That's right.

124
00:07:26,110 --> 00:07:27,480
Hello.

125
00:07:27,570 --> 00:07:31,690
Squid and mackerel are extra fresh today.

126
00:07:31,780 --> 00:07:33,650
-What would you like?
-Well…

127
00:07:34,240 --> 00:07:36,820
Are you Sun-young's mother?

128
00:07:36,910 --> 00:07:38,370
-I…
-What is it?

129
00:07:38,450 --> 00:07:41,660
Did that bitch
run off with your money too?

130
00:07:42,870 --> 00:07:45,630
-Sorry?
-That crazy bitch!

131
00:07:46,630 --> 00:07:50,630
I can't live like this!

132
00:07:50,710 --> 00:07:51,920
Good grief!

133
00:07:53,380 --> 00:07:57,720
She met this gigolo somewhere

134
00:07:57,800 --> 00:08:01,060
and gave him every single penny she had.

135
00:08:01,140 --> 00:08:05,480
Then she even took out a private loan
to pay back his gambling debt.

136
00:08:05,560 --> 00:08:06,560
Good grief.

137
00:08:07,440 --> 00:08:09,020
She put up her home, salon,

138
00:08:09,110 --> 00:08:12,240
and even her father's fishing boat
as collateral.

139
00:08:12,320 --> 00:08:14,610
Goodness me.

140
00:08:15,400 --> 00:08:17,030
That darned brat

141
00:08:17,110 --> 00:08:19,700
never even called me once after that,

142
00:08:19,780 --> 00:08:22,410
then texted me saying
she was going to Los Angeles

143
00:08:22,500 --> 00:08:24,460
or whatever to make money.

144
00:08:24,540 --> 00:08:25,830
Good grief.

145
00:08:25,920 --> 00:08:29,710
All she left was that one message
before she disappeared.

146
00:08:34,510 --> 00:08:37,340
-What do I do?
-I raised her wrong.

147
00:08:37,430 --> 00:08:39,970
Who else is to blame?

148
00:08:40,050 --> 00:08:42,100
You can just take me.

149
00:08:42,180 --> 00:08:44,180
Just take me away!

150
00:08:45,640 --> 00:08:47,100
No.

151
00:08:48,060 --> 00:08:51,730
It must've been so tough for you.

152
00:08:52,650 --> 00:08:55,320
You're much better than my daughter.

153
00:08:55,400 --> 00:08:58,450
Just be my daughter!

154
00:08:58,530 --> 00:09:00,950
Mom!

155
00:09:10,290 --> 00:09:14,090
LEGAL PROCEEDINGS WILL BE INITIATED
DUE TO LONG OVERDUE PAYMENTS.

156
00:09:14,960 --> 00:09:16,470
LANDLADY

157
00:09:18,880 --> 00:09:20,140
Hello, ma'am.

158
00:09:20,220 --> 00:09:21,680
Are you really going to be like this?

159
00:09:22,470 --> 00:09:25,350
I even gave you back
your deposit in advance.

160
00:09:25,930 --> 00:09:28,440
Your rent payments have been long overdue.

161
00:09:29,100 --> 00:09:30,400
I can't wait any longer.

162
00:09:30,480 --> 00:09:33,150
I'm going to vacate the place
if you don't transfer the money by today.

163
00:09:33,230 --> 00:09:34,440
Well, I…

164
00:09:47,370 --> 00:09:50,170
SEO-JIN, YE-JIN
I MADE THIS BANKBOOK FOR YOU

165
00:09:51,790 --> 00:09:54,380
I WANT TO LET YOU DO
EVERYTHING YOU WANT

166
00:09:56,670 --> 00:09:58,630
YE-JIN, SEO-JIN
GIVE MOM THE POWER TO GO ON

167
00:10:25,280 --> 00:10:26,290
Stay there.

168
00:10:27,950 --> 00:10:31,120
A warm welcome
to Petit Nail, Sillim Branch!

169
00:10:33,080 --> 00:10:35,000
How many years of experience do you have?

170
00:10:35,630 --> 00:10:37,380
I got certified in school

171
00:10:37,460 --> 00:10:39,470
and worked at the Ewha Branch
for three and a half years.

172
00:10:39,550 --> 00:10:42,390
And I'm joining this branch
because I moved to Sillim-dong.

173
00:10:42,470 --> 00:10:43,640
Welcome.

174
00:10:43,720 --> 00:10:45,180
Your manager told us

175
00:10:45,260 --> 00:10:49,140
you were popular among college girls
for your quick hands and nail arts.

176
00:10:49,230 --> 00:10:50,850
I look forward to working with you.

177
00:10:50,940 --> 00:10:52,140
Yes, I'll do my best.

178
00:10:53,350 --> 00:10:54,770
-My gosh.
-It's here.

179
00:10:54,860 --> 00:10:56,230
The raw fish here is delicious.

180
00:10:56,320 --> 00:10:59,440
The owner catches the fish himself.

181
00:10:59,530 --> 00:11:01,950
So this is caught in the wild?

182
00:11:05,490 --> 00:11:06,450
Kang-ho?

183
00:11:06,530 --> 00:11:08,120
No, not kelpfish. It's rockfish.

184
00:11:08,200 --> 00:11:09,540
Wild rockfish.

185
00:11:09,620 --> 00:11:11,120
A bottle of soju, please.

186
00:11:11,210 --> 00:11:12,160
Mi-joo?

187
00:11:12,250 --> 00:11:13,710
No, not Mi-joo. Soju.

188
00:11:28,720 --> 00:11:31,680
Where have you been, you jerk?

189
00:11:43,030 --> 00:11:46,620
I can't believe you've never called
after moving to Seoul.

190
00:11:48,200 --> 00:11:49,540
I waited for so long.

191
00:11:50,160 --> 00:11:52,710
Why didn't you call first?

192
00:11:52,790 --> 00:11:54,710
I didn't have your number.

193
00:11:55,290 --> 00:11:57,000
Your mom wouldn't tell me either.

194
00:11:57,540 --> 00:11:59,250
You knew the school I was attending.

195
00:11:59,340 --> 00:12:01,130
I wanted to look for you.

196
00:12:02,760 --> 00:12:04,130
But I couldn't.

197
00:12:05,340 --> 00:12:07,510
You ruined your exam because of me.

198
00:12:08,180 --> 00:12:09,640
I couldn't ruin anything more.

199
00:12:13,600 --> 00:12:14,560
Wait.

200
00:12:17,350 --> 00:12:19,980
Did you give up on the bar exam?

201
00:12:21,650 --> 00:12:23,690
I took the first test yesterday.

202
00:12:24,400 --> 00:12:26,450
Isn't it a little too early to give up?

203
00:12:27,160 --> 00:12:28,280
I see.

204
00:12:30,780 --> 00:12:32,160
Then what are you doing here?

205
00:12:33,040 --> 00:12:33,910
Working a part-time job.

206
00:12:34,000 --> 00:12:36,460
Shouldn't you be studying every second?

207
00:12:36,540 --> 00:12:38,630
I'm doing this to survive.

208
00:12:38,710 --> 00:12:40,710
I have to make a living too.

209
00:12:40,790 --> 00:12:43,590
What do you mean?
Doesn't your mom help you?

210
00:12:45,550 --> 00:12:48,390
I'm old enough to look after myself.

211
00:12:48,470 --> 00:12:50,260
But every second counts for you.

212
00:12:50,850 --> 00:12:53,350
If I fail the exam
because of a part-time job,

213
00:12:53,430 --> 00:12:55,430
it means I'm just not good enough.

214
00:12:56,770 --> 00:12:58,150
Don't worry.

215
00:12:58,230 --> 00:13:00,400
It's a restaurant, so I get free food,

216
00:13:00,480 --> 00:13:02,530
the lady here sometimes
helps with my laundry,

217
00:13:03,360 --> 00:13:05,570
and on weekends, I get to go fishing too.

218
00:13:06,780 --> 00:13:07,860
Above all,

219
00:13:09,700 --> 00:13:12,030
I like looking at these fish.

220
00:13:13,910 --> 00:13:16,120
What's great about staring at fish
that are about to die?

221
00:13:16,210 --> 00:13:17,370
Exactly.

222
00:13:18,580 --> 00:13:20,880
They might die any moment now,

223
00:13:20,960 --> 00:13:23,380
but no matter how painful or scary it is,

224
00:13:23,960 --> 00:13:25,670
they're unable to cry or scream.

225
00:13:27,680 --> 00:13:29,640
I think judicial officers
must be like that.

226
00:13:31,140 --> 00:13:34,470
You hated how your fate was decided
the moment you were born.

227
00:13:36,020 --> 00:13:38,060
I guess you've changed your mind.

228
00:13:39,270 --> 00:13:40,270
No.

229
00:13:41,690 --> 00:13:42,770
Nothing's changed.

230
00:13:43,690 --> 00:13:46,190
I still hate it,
and it's still a heavy burden.

231
00:13:46,780 --> 00:13:50,740
But I hate this heavy burden so much that
I'll make sure I make it.

232
00:13:51,620 --> 00:13:55,330
That's the revenge for my fate,
which was already decided

233
00:13:55,410 --> 00:13:57,120
the moment I was born.

234
00:14:06,420 --> 00:14:08,880
So, Mi-joo, how are you doing?
How's your job?

235
00:14:15,890 --> 00:14:18,100
Things have never gone well for me,

236
00:14:18,180 --> 00:14:20,310
and I never had a reason to be successful.

237
00:14:21,400 --> 00:14:22,860
But from now, I'm going to do well.

238
00:14:24,650 --> 00:14:26,530
I just found something I want to do.

239
00:14:28,110 --> 00:14:29,950
You just focus on your studies.

240
00:14:30,530 --> 00:14:33,620
You might be able to pass it
with the top score if you don't work.

241
00:14:34,120 --> 00:14:35,620
Let me invest in you.

242
00:14:36,830 --> 00:14:39,910
I don't have much right now,
so I'll start with myself.

243
00:14:41,830 --> 00:14:44,290
Let me help you get your revenge.

244
00:14:51,180 --> 00:14:52,760
Thank you for everything.

245
00:14:53,680 --> 00:14:55,470
We never had any kids,

246
00:14:56,260 --> 00:14:58,020
so you were like a son to us.

247
00:14:58,100 --> 00:14:59,180
This is so sad.

248
00:15:00,060 --> 00:15:01,730
Don't be so sad.

249
00:15:01,810 --> 00:15:04,810
He'll study hard
and become a judicial officer.

250
00:15:05,900 --> 00:15:07,900
Come and visit me

251
00:15:07,980 --> 00:15:09,490
when you need to blow off steam.

252
00:15:09,570 --> 00:15:10,530
I'll give you a ride.

253
00:15:11,240 --> 00:15:13,490
Yes, I'll do that. Thank you.

254
00:15:13,570 --> 00:15:15,240
Future judicial officer, Kang-ho!

255
00:15:15,320 --> 00:15:17,240
You got this!

256
00:15:22,920 --> 00:15:24,170
Did you talk to them?

257
00:15:24,250 --> 00:15:26,750
Yes, it went well.

258
00:15:27,710 --> 00:15:29,250
-Wait, they'll see us.
-What?

259
00:15:31,420 --> 00:15:32,800
Wait for me!

260
00:15:49,190 --> 00:15:50,110
Focus!

261
00:15:51,570 --> 00:15:52,820
Mi-joo.

262
00:16:03,210 --> 00:16:05,500
Kang-ho, I'll wash these too.

263
00:16:08,790 --> 00:16:10,380
-No! It's okay.
-Let me.

264
00:16:10,460 --> 00:16:12,590
-No!
-There's another one.

265
00:16:12,670 --> 00:16:16,680
PETIT NAIL

266
00:16:16,760 --> 00:16:17,590
Mi-joo.

267
00:16:17,680 --> 00:16:18,550
Yes?

268
00:16:23,810 --> 00:16:25,600
YOU HAVE PASSED THE 1ST TEST

269
00:16:26,520 --> 00:16:27,440
Really?

270
00:16:27,520 --> 00:16:29,190
My gosh!

271
00:16:33,320 --> 00:16:35,570
BAR EXAM MEAL

272
00:16:37,700 --> 00:16:39,870
Hey. What is that?

