472
00:27:43,200 --> 00:27:46,160
to eventually approach me.

473
00:27:47,910 --> 00:27:50,080
Choi Kang-ho already knew everything.

474
00:27:50,700 --> 00:27:55,290
He knew who killed his father

475
00:27:56,670 --> 00:27:57,920
thirty years ago.

476
00:28:00,380 --> 00:28:03,050
Who killed his father?

477
00:28:03,130 --> 00:28:05,340
He's Choi Hae-sik's son.

478
00:28:05,430 --> 00:28:06,720
Choi Kang-ho.

479
00:28:06,800 --> 00:28:07,800
Exactly.

480
00:28:09,350 --> 00:28:12,890
Who killed Choi Kang-ho's father,
Choi Hae-sik?

481
00:28:13,730 --> 00:28:15,150
Did you kill him?

482
00:28:16,650 --> 00:28:17,900
You did.

483
00:28:18,610 --> 00:28:19,900
Oh, my.

484
00:28:20,780 --> 00:28:21,990
Did I kill him?

485
00:28:22,990 --> 00:28:24,030
Really?

486
00:28:25,280 --> 00:28:27,660
I didn't know
because there was no evidence.

487
00:28:29,910 --> 00:28:32,160
But isn't this odd?

488
00:28:32,250 --> 00:28:35,290
A kid who wanted to
take revenge on his father's killer

489
00:28:35,370 --> 00:28:38,920
