519
00:30:29,450 --> 00:30:30,450
So,

520
00:30:30,530 --> 00:30:33,830
what does your father do?

521
00:30:35,870 --> 00:30:37,330
He passed away.

522
00:30:39,210 --> 00:30:40,870
Goodness.

523
00:30:41,370 --> 00:30:43,330
I shouldn't have asked.

524
00:30:44,460 --> 00:30:45,380
I'm sorry.

525
00:30:46,050 --> 00:30:47,090
It's all right.

526
00:30:47,630 --> 00:30:49,550
He passed away before I was born.

527
00:30:49,630 --> 00:30:51,590
I don't have any memories of him.

528
00:30:51,680 --> 00:30:52,970
He passed away…

529
00:30:53,760 --> 00:30:55,220
even before you were born?

530
00:30:55,930 --> 00:30:58,680
He must have passed away
at a very young age.

531
00:30:58,770 --> 00:30:59,850
What happened?

532
00:31:02,850 --> 00:31:05,360
I heard he took his own life.

533
00:31:05,440 --> 00:31:06,440
Suicide?

534
00:31:07,320 --> 00:31:08,690
Why did he do that?

535
00:31:08,780 --> 00:31:11,200
His farm went under after a fire,

536
00:31:11,910 --> 00:31:14,530
and he was apparently
under a lot of stress.

537
00:31:15,200 --> 00:31:16,910
I don't know anything more.

538
00:31:19,160 --> 00:31:20,120
Well…

539
00:31:21,000 --> 00:31:24,460
To be frank, I don't want to know.

540
00:31:26,000 --> 00:31:28,000
To me, my father

541
00:31:28,090 --> 00:31:30,720
is just an irresponsible man

542
00:31:31,420 --> 00:31:33,260
who abandoned his wife and unborn child.

543
00:31:37,140 --> 00:31:40,350
Anyhow, I'm sorry.

544
00:31:41,310 --> 00:31:43,190
Have a drink with me.

545
00:31:56,370 --> 00:31:58,700
Prosecutor Choi, let me ask you something.

546
00:31:58,790 --> 00:32:00,200
What's the reason?

547
00:32:01,200 --> 00:32:03,830
-Sorry?
-This trial, I mean.

548
00:32:04,420 --> 00:32:07,040
Are you after money or power?

549
00:32:09,170 --> 00:32:10,340
If I want it,

550
00:32:11,460 --> 00:32:12,880
can you give it to me?

551
00:32:14,430 --> 00:32:16,590
You just saved my grandson.

552
00:32:16,680 --> 00:32:18,140
So why not?

553
00:32:22,100 --> 00:32:23,940
In that case, both.

554
00:32:26,980 --> 00:32:27,810
Man.

555
00:32:27,900 --> 00:32:30,020
You're a man, aren't you?

556
00:32:30,860 --> 00:32:32,110
Mr. So.

557
00:32:36,070 --> 00:32:37,070
Go on.

558
00:32:46,250 --> 00:32:48,420
In return, from now on,

559
00:32:48,500 --> 00:32:50,420
you'll be a part of my family.

560
00:32:53,510 --> 00:32:54,630
Thank you.

561
00:32:57,640 --> 00:32:58,590
Thank you.

562
00:32:58,680 --> 00:32:59,640
Thank you very much.

563
00:33:00,390 --> 00:33:01,680
That's enough.

564
00:33:02,720 --> 00:33:05,270
I'll do my best, Mr. Song. Thank you!

565
00:33:05,350 --> 00:33:09,730
I don't care what Kang-ho had on his mind

566
00:33:09,810 --> 00:33:11,270
when he approached me.

567
00:33:11,360 --> 00:33:14,070
I don't care if it's ambition or wrath.

568
00:33:15,070 --> 00:33:17,660
Because his hands are now also dirty.

569
00:33:18,240 --> 00:33:21,530
All I want to do is use his talent

570
00:33:22,290 --> 00:33:25,460
and then I'll abandon him.

571
00:33:38,680 --> 00:33:40,090
Goodness, Mr. Son.

572
00:33:40,720 --> 00:33:43,930
What on earth are you doing?
It's been an hour.

573
00:33:44,020 --> 00:33:49,100
It's because my breathing rhythm is off.

574
00:33:49,190 --> 00:33:50,060
I'm sorry.

575
00:33:50,150 --> 00:33:52,940
This time, I'll really insert it.

576
00:34:07,460 --> 00:34:08,500
Damn it.

577
00:34:08,580 --> 00:34:11,210
Even fish don't breathe like that.

578
00:34:12,380 --> 00:34:13,420
Mr. Son.

579
00:34:13,920 --> 00:34:17,510
Are you really a licensed doctor?

580
00:34:17,590 --> 00:34:19,220
I'm getting a bit anxious.

581
00:34:19,300 --> 00:34:20,640
Goodness.

582
00:34:23,050 --> 00:34:25,180
-Oh, my! What are you doing?
-Kang-ho.

583
00:34:25,260 --> 00:34:26,680
My mom feels anxious.

584
00:34:26,770 --> 00:34:29,560
No, Kang-ho.
That's dangerous. Give it to me.

585
00:34:30,390 --> 00:34:31,730
Are you really licensed?

586
00:34:31,810 --> 00:34:34,610
I really am! What's with you?

587
00:34:35,360 --> 00:34:37,570
Honey, tell him.

588
00:34:37,650 --> 00:34:38,570
He is.

589
00:34:39,150 --> 00:34:42,030
He would never forge a license.

590
00:34:42,620 --> 00:34:45,280
Although he has forged
his resident registration card before.

591
00:34:45,870 --> 00:34:47,330
-What?
-What?

592
00:34:48,620 --> 00:34:50,080
I did it because I love you!

593
00:34:51,210 --> 00:34:53,710
I thought that was how I could have you!

594
00:34:53,790 --> 00:34:54,840
You're my woman!

595
00:34:55,920 --> 00:34:58,420
I thought you might not like me
because of our age gap.

596
00:34:58,510 --> 00:35:01,470
Oh, my. Is that really why?

597
00:35:02,390 --> 00:35:04,260
Did you want me that badly?

598
00:35:07,270 --> 00:35:08,310
Good grief.

599
00:35:08,390 --> 00:35:09,770
How is that relevant right now?

600
00:35:11,190 --> 00:35:12,600
He'll bleed if you stab him.

601
00:35:12,690 --> 00:35:15,820
That'll make me sad.
Do you want me to be sad?

602
00:35:22,410 --> 00:35:23,530
Good boy.

603
00:35:23,610 --> 00:35:25,240
-Good boy.
-Good, Kang-ho.

604
00:35:25,320 --> 00:35:27,450
-Good boy.
-You must've been startled.

605
00:35:28,580 --> 00:35:29,660
-It's okay.
-I'm sorry.

606
00:35:29,750 --> 00:35:31,290
No, it's fine.

607
00:35:31,370 --> 00:35:34,670
You can feel that way
if he doesn't seem very trustworthy.

608
00:35:39,210 --> 00:35:41,630
By any chance, do you know

609
00:35:41,720 --> 00:35:44,890
a man named Choi Mun-sik,
who owns a carp farm in Negi-ri?

610
00:35:52,440 --> 00:35:53,270
Hello?

611
00:35:54,520 --> 00:35:55,650
The realtor?

612
00:35:57,610 --> 00:35:58,770
Yes, one second.

613
00:35:58,860 --> 00:36:00,900
Was it Choi Mun-sik?

614
00:36:00,990 --> 00:36:02,860
-Isn't it Yoo Mun-sik?
-Not Lee?

615
00:36:02,950 --> 00:36:04,360
No, he's Choi Mun-sik.

616
00:36:04,450 --> 00:36:07,280
Yes, that huge carp farm in Negi-ri.
Of course, I know.

617
00:36:07,370 --> 00:36:08,830
I've heard of him too.

618
00:36:09,620 --> 00:36:11,620
We know. Go on.

619
00:36:12,330 --> 00:36:13,330
What's with him?

620
00:36:15,710 --> 00:36:18,210
Mr. Son, go on and talk.

621
00:36:18,290 --> 00:36:20,130
Go on and talk, Mr. Son.

622
00:36:20,760 --> 00:36:21,760
Mr. Son…

623
00:36:22,260 --> 00:36:23,300
What's with him?

624
00:36:23,380 --> 00:36:26,390
So that Choi Mun-sik--

625
00:36:26,470 --> 00:36:28,350
I have to go to Seoul tomorrow.

626
00:36:29,060 --> 00:36:31,930
Seoul? What for?

627
00:36:33,560 --> 00:36:37,270
I'm sorry I keep asking you guys
for favors like this.

628
00:36:37,360 --> 00:36:41,070
Don't say that. We're neighbors.

629
00:36:41,150 --> 00:36:42,400
Don't worry.

630
00:36:42,490 --> 00:36:45,200
We'll give the pigs their meals
and Kang-ho his feed…

631
00:36:50,910 --> 00:36:54,460
We'll make sure Kang-ho has his meal
and the pigs their feed.

632
00:36:54,540 --> 00:36:56,120
Don't worry about a thing.

633
00:36:56,920 --> 00:36:59,710
Okay. Andrea's got the farm covered,

634
00:36:59,790 --> 00:37:01,460
so please just look after Kang-ho.

635
00:37:02,050 --> 00:37:03,050
I'll get going then.

636
00:37:05,470 --> 00:37:06,430
Right.

637
00:37:07,130 --> 00:37:09,510
Kang-ho, I'll come back soon

638
00:37:09,600 --> 00:37:11,930
after I get your stuff.

639
00:37:12,680 --> 00:37:15,020
I'll go with you and come back with you.

640
00:37:15,520 --> 00:37:16,440
Kang-ho.

641
00:37:18,770 --> 00:37:20,060
I told you, didn't I?

642
00:37:20,150 --> 00:37:23,570
The place is really dusty
because people are moving things.

643
00:37:24,110 --> 00:37:27,150
If dust gets into your body,
you'll get sick.

644
00:37:27,990 --> 00:37:29,870
And that'll make me really sad.

645
00:37:30,450 --> 00:37:31,950
Do you want me to be sad?

646
00:37:32,620 --> 00:37:33,540
No.

647
00:37:38,870 --> 00:37:40,420
How soon will you come back?

648
00:37:43,460 --> 00:37:44,460
Around five o'clock.

649
00:37:45,170 --> 00:37:46,630
-Five o'clock.
-Yes.

650
00:37:47,590 --> 00:37:51,010
So be good and do as they say, okay?

651
00:37:51,100 --> 00:37:52,890
Make sure you study and exercise.

652
00:37:54,180 --> 00:37:55,600
-Okay.
-Good.

653
00:37:56,270 --> 00:37:58,440
WE'RE ALL JOU-RI FAMILY

654
00:38:15,240 --> 00:38:17,040
I told you, didn't I?

655
00:38:17,120 --> 00:38:19,250
I told you he'd be doing something stupid.

656
00:38:20,210 --> 00:38:21,500
Why are you here?

657
00:38:21,580 --> 00:38:24,590
I heard Ms. Jin
is coming back at five o'clock.

658
00:38:25,550 --> 00:38:26,510
Yes.

659
00:38:27,380 --> 00:38:30,130
So what time is five o'clock?

660
00:38:30,800 --> 00:38:34,260
We're only seven,
so we can't read the clock,

661
00:38:34,350 --> 00:38:38,430
but I do know that we have
a lot of time to play with him.

662
00:38:38,520 --> 00:38:40,270
-Yes!
-Yes!

663
00:38:40,350 --> 00:38:42,520
No, I can't play today.

664
00:38:43,110 --> 00:38:45,690
I have to study and exercise.

665
00:38:45,780 --> 00:38:47,440
Study? We'll help you.

666
00:38:48,280 --> 00:38:49,110
Exercise?

667
00:38:49,200 --> 00:38:51,610
You know we're experts at that.

668
00:38:52,200 --> 00:38:53,700
-Let's play!
-No! I can't!

669
00:38:53,780 --> 00:38:56,040
-Let's play!
-No! I can't play right now!

670
00:38:56,120 --> 00:38:57,450
No!

671
00:38:57,540 --> 00:38:59,580
No!

672
00:39:22,230 --> 00:39:26,230
I left everything as is
because I thought you would return soon.

673
00:39:28,070 --> 00:39:31,070
But the realtor called and said
your lease has expired.

674
00:39:31,150 --> 00:39:32,660
CHOI KANG-HO
SUPREME PROSECUTORS' OFFICE

675
00:39:32,740 --> 00:39:34,240
I'm sorry, Kang-ho.

676
00:39:43,370 --> 00:39:45,290
I've always wanted to visit this place.

677
00:39:48,050 --> 00:39:49,710
And I'm finally here.

678
00:40:01,100 --> 00:40:02,600
Are you taking this painting?

679
00:40:04,350 --> 00:40:05,350
This is…

680
00:40:06,150 --> 00:40:07,730
-Sure.
-Okay.

681
00:40:22,040 --> 00:40:24,000
He had some things here too.

682
00:40:27,710 --> 00:40:29,300
MY SON, JUNG JONG-GU, IS INNOCENT!

683
00:40:29,380 --> 00:40:31,340
I DENOUNCE PROSECUTOR CHOI KANG-HO!

684
00:40:38,850 --> 00:40:40,260
He doesn't have a lot here.

685
00:40:40,850 --> 00:40:45,020
I put his personal belongings in here.

686
00:40:45,100 --> 00:40:46,230
And… Right.

687
00:40:46,310 --> 00:40:48,230
That plant pot is his too.

688
00:40:50,820 --> 00:40:53,490
It looks dead, so you can leave it.
We'll throw it out.

689
00:40:53,570 --> 00:40:54,650
No.

690
00:40:55,320 --> 00:40:58,200
It's not dead.

691
00:40:58,280 --> 00:41:00,120
The stem looks perfectly fine.

692
00:41:00,740 --> 00:41:02,290
I'll take it.

693
00:41:03,200 --> 00:41:05,040
Why didn't anyone water this?

694
00:41:06,830 --> 00:41:09,420
You can't go in there.
Ma'am, please leave.

695
00:41:09,500 --> 00:41:10,460
Please.

696
00:41:11,130 --> 00:41:13,880
Where's Choi Kang-ho? Where is he?

697
00:41:14,470 --> 00:41:15,880
Woobyeok Group bought him off, right?

698
00:41:16,470 --> 00:41:17,930
That's why the case was acquitted!

699
00:41:18,010 --> 00:41:19,390
My daughter is the evidence!

700
00:41:19,470 --> 00:41:22,100
So how is it that the case is dismissed
for lack of evidence?

701
00:41:22,180 --> 00:41:23,810
Ma'am, you can't do this here!

702
00:41:23,890 --> 00:41:26,730
If you don't stop, we'll arrest you
for obstruction of justice.

703
00:41:26,810 --> 00:41:27,850
Come on.

704
00:41:27,940 --> 00:41:29,400
Where is Choi Kang-ho?

705
00:41:29,480 --> 00:41:30,690
Please leave.

706
00:41:30,770 --> 00:41:32,690
Where is he?

707
00:41:32,780 --> 00:41:33,820
Please leave.

708
00:41:35,740 --> 00:41:39,030
What was that woman talking about?

709
00:41:44,160 --> 00:41:45,870
MY SON, JUNG JONG-GU, IS INNOCENT!

710
00:41:45,960 --> 00:41:47,620
I DENOUNCE PROSECUTOR CHOI KANG-HO!

711
00:41:57,170 --> 00:41:58,050
Excuse me.

712
00:41:59,340 --> 00:42:00,760
Why are you doing this?

713
00:42:01,970 --> 00:42:04,640
What did my son do so wrong
for you to do this here?

714
00:42:05,680 --> 00:42:08,520
Are you Prosecutor Choi Kang-ho's mother?

715
00:42:08,600 --> 00:42:10,400
Yes, I'm his mother.

716
00:42:11,150 --> 00:42:12,690
If you feel something is unfair,

717
00:42:12,770 --> 00:42:15,610
you should go through the legal process
and get a retrial.

718
00:42:15,690 --> 00:42:18,900
Why on earth are you
condemning my son so harshly?

719
00:42:21,030 --> 00:42:23,620
What's wrong with you? Give it back!

720
00:42:24,160 --> 00:42:25,200
Give it back!

721
00:42:30,370 --> 00:42:31,460
My son

722
00:42:32,040 --> 00:42:33,960
has a physical disability.

723
00:42:35,090 --> 00:42:38,510
He couldn't even hurt a fly.

724
00:42:39,220 --> 00:42:43,970
Your son knew that,
but he took a bribe from a rich man

725
00:42:44,050 --> 00:42:46,430
and turned my son into a murderer.

726
00:42:46,520 --> 00:42:49,440
When my husband asked to hear him out,

727
00:42:49,520 --> 00:42:52,310
he said such harsh things
and made him collapse.

728
00:42:52,860 --> 00:42:54,900
Your son is such a horrible person.

729
00:42:54,980 --> 00:42:58,400
Why did you give birth to such scum?

730
00:42:58,490 --> 00:42:59,450
Darn it!

731
00:42:59,530 --> 00:43:01,860
I will make your son pay for it!

732
00:43:02,450 --> 00:43:05,450
I may forget to eat,

733
00:43:06,240 --> 00:43:10,330
but I will not forget to pray that

734
00:43:11,080 --> 00:43:13,670
your son gets punished and dies!

735
00:43:14,170 --> 00:43:16,420
You got that?

736
00:43:16,500 --> 00:43:18,510
Why should my son get punished?

737
00:43:19,380 --> 00:43:21,720
Your son should be punished for his crime.

738
00:43:22,300 --> 00:43:23,840
He was bribed?

739
00:43:24,510 --> 00:43:26,600
Why would he? What more could he want?

740
00:43:27,100 --> 00:43:29,430
Did you see him take it?

741
00:43:30,600 --> 00:43:33,190
If you say anything of this sort again,

742
00:43:33,730 --> 00:43:36,070
I will make you pay for it.

743
00:43:36,150 --> 00:43:37,150
Understand?

744
00:43:37,230 --> 00:43:38,110
All right.

745
00:43:38,820 --> 00:43:39,990
Kill me.

746
00:43:40,070 --> 00:43:41,200
Just kill me.

747
00:43:42,490 --> 00:43:43,490
Kill me!

748
00:43:45,410 --> 00:43:47,410
My poor son…

749
00:43:47,490 --> 00:43:50,290
Now, the next one is a science question.

750
00:43:50,370 --> 00:43:52,160
This insect lives in a flower.

751
00:43:53,460 --> 00:43:54,290
Butterfly.

752
00:43:54,380 --> 00:43:55,330
Wrong.

753
00:43:56,170 --> 00:43:57,710
-Bee.
-Wrong.

754
00:43:57,800 --> 00:43:58,630
What?

755
00:43:59,210 --> 00:44:02,760
Silverfish, cabbage caterpillars,
fleas, and aphids.

756
00:44:02,840 --> 00:44:04,300
Correct!

757
00:44:04,390 --> 00:44:06,550
I was actually talking
about napa cabbage flowers.

758
00:44:06,640 --> 00:44:08,430
Okay, ten points to Lee Seo-jin.

759
00:44:09,720 --> 00:44:12,390
Hey, Ye-jin, that's not right.

760
00:44:12,480 --> 00:44:14,940
He mentioned four.
That means he gets forty points.

761
00:44:18,610 --> 00:44:20,360
Okay. He can get 40 points.

762
00:44:21,650 --> 00:44:22,950
That could've been bad, right?

763
00:44:23,030 --> 00:44:25,320
Right, sure.

764
00:44:26,870 --> 00:44:29,370
Okay, the next one is a math question.

765
00:44:29,450 --> 00:44:32,410
Seo-jin had five apples.

766
00:44:33,000 --> 00:44:36,210
But Ye-jin stole three. How many are left?

767
00:44:37,460 --> 00:44:38,540
Kang-ho was faster.

768
00:44:41,050 --> 00:44:43,380
Simple larceny shall be punished
for up to six years

769
00:44:43,470 --> 00:44:47,930
or by a fine under ten million won
under Article 329 of the Criminal Act.

770
00:44:51,010 --> 00:44:53,680
What's simple larceny?

771
00:44:55,310 --> 00:44:56,270
What?

772
00:44:57,150 --> 00:44:58,690
What's simple larceny?

773
00:45:02,780 --> 00:45:03,820
Catch it!

774
00:45:05,360 --> 00:45:06,820
Oh, no. She's mad.

775
00:45:10,530 --> 00:45:12,240
You should have caught it.

776
00:45:12,830 --> 00:45:15,080
My mom sent it to us from the US.

777
00:45:15,160 --> 00:45:17,000
You almost lost it!

778
00:45:17,670 --> 00:45:19,590
-The US?
-Yes, the US.

779
00:45:19,670 --> 00:45:20,500
Look.

780
00:45:20,590 --> 00:45:21,750
It's written in English.

781
00:45:21,840 --> 00:45:23,550
"From the US."

782
00:45:24,920 --> 00:45:25,880
Sorry.

783
00:45:25,970 --> 00:45:29,800
Anyway, I'll get really mad
if you miss the ball again.

784
00:45:30,390 --> 00:45:31,760
-Okay.
-All right.

785
00:45:31,850 --> 00:45:32,930
Play ball!

786
00:45:40,020 --> 00:45:41,110
Strike!

787
00:45:41,190 --> 00:45:42,190
Hey, Ye-jin.

788
00:45:42,270 --> 00:45:44,440
-That's a strike?
-Yes.

789
00:45:45,820 --> 00:45:47,740
You're really good at baseball.

790
00:45:48,320 --> 00:45:49,490
Did your dad teach you?

791
00:45:53,290 --> 00:45:55,450
Don't ever mention my dad again,

792
00:45:55,540 --> 00:45:57,080
especially before my grandma.

793
00:45:58,040 --> 00:45:58,920
Why not?

794
00:45:59,000 --> 00:46:00,830
This is a huge secret.

795
00:46:01,630 --> 00:46:03,500
Actually, my dad is…

796
00:46:07,930 --> 00:46:10,050
What? Your dad is a horrifying bastard?

797
00:46:12,140 --> 00:46:13,470
I'm sure of it.

798
00:46:13,560 --> 00:46:17,230
My grandma said that countless times.

799
00:46:18,100 --> 00:46:19,810
But what's a horrifying bastard?

800
00:46:24,980 --> 00:46:26,240
Tell him.

801
00:46:28,740 --> 00:46:31,820
Do you know what horrifying means?

802
00:46:32,570 --> 00:46:35,580
It means scary in other words.

803
00:46:36,200 --> 00:46:41,500
So it means our dad
is someone who's really scary.

804
00:46:41,580 --> 00:46:43,380
-I see.
-He's so scary that

805
00:46:43,460 --> 00:46:45,840
my grandma shudders

806
00:46:45,920 --> 00:46:48,760
whenever she mentions him.

807
00:46:48,840 --> 00:46:52,680
I even saw her eyes turn white.

808
00:46:52,760 --> 00:46:54,470
He must be really scary.

809
00:46:55,060 --> 00:46:57,850
So you better behave.

810
00:46:57,930 --> 00:47:00,690
If you don't, we'll tell on you

811
00:47:00,770 --> 00:47:02,850
to our horrible bastard dad!

812
00:47:03,440 --> 00:47:04,650
Understood?

813
00:47:04,730 --> 00:47:05,610
Yes, ma'am.

814
00:47:05,690 --> 00:47:08,690
Come on. You don't have to be so polite.

815
00:47:09,400 --> 00:47:10,360
Okay.

816
00:47:10,450 --> 00:47:13,320
All right, let's get back to baseball.

817
00:47:13,410 --> 00:47:14,620
All right.

818
00:47:26,800 --> 00:47:27,710
No!

819
00:47:36,850 --> 00:47:38,970
-All safe?
-Yes, I'm fine.

820
00:47:39,060 --> 00:47:40,680
I'm talking about the ball!

821
00:47:40,770 --> 00:47:43,020
Is my bouncy ball safe?

822
00:47:43,100 --> 00:47:43,940
No way.

823
00:47:45,730 --> 00:47:47,770
Choi Kang-ho!

824
00:47:47,860 --> 00:47:51,530
How dare you lose my bouncy ball?

825
00:47:52,150 --> 00:47:53,030
My…

826
00:47:53,700 --> 00:47:54,820
My dad

827
00:47:54,910 --> 00:47:57,700
will come and teach you a lesson!

828
00:47:57,780 --> 00:47:59,870
Ye-jin, wait!

829
00:47:59,950 --> 00:48:01,000
Seo-jin!

830
00:48:02,370 --> 00:48:05,130
Kang-ho would never do
something like that.

831
00:48:05,210 --> 00:48:08,550
Things like that happen from time to time
when a trial doesn't go well.

832
00:48:08,630 --> 00:48:09,670
Don't worry about it.

833
00:48:15,720 --> 00:48:16,760
No.

834
00:48:30,280 --> 00:48:31,490
Goodness.

835
00:48:34,360 --> 00:48:35,360
Are you all right?

836
00:48:35,450 --> 00:48:37,030
Of course not. How can I be fine?

837
00:48:42,000 --> 00:48:43,460
What are you doing?

838
00:48:44,000 --> 00:48:46,420
Lady, what do you think?

839
00:48:46,500 --> 00:48:48,540
I'm taking a photo of the assailant.

840
00:48:48,630 --> 00:48:50,250
What do you mean?

841
00:48:50,340 --> 00:48:54,590
Look how much damage
your beat-up truck caused

842
00:48:54,680 --> 00:48:57,010
to my expensive foreign car.

843
00:48:57,090 --> 00:48:59,390
You hit me from the back.

844
00:48:59,470 --> 00:49:01,890
I don't want to hear it.

845
00:49:02,470 --> 00:49:04,180
I'll settle for 50 million won.

846
00:49:04,270 --> 00:49:06,940
If anything, I should be saying that!

847
00:49:07,020 --> 00:49:08,560
Forget it. I'll call the police.

848
00:49:08,650 --> 00:49:10,110
The police? Listen, lady.

849
00:49:10,690 --> 00:49:12,320
Do you really want to go to prison?

850
00:49:12,400 --> 00:49:14,400
Why would I go to prison?

851
00:49:14,490 --> 00:49:16,910
You should keep
a safe distance when you drive!

852
00:49:16,990 --> 00:49:19,320
Safe distance, my foot.

853
00:49:19,410 --> 00:49:23,290
If you can't drive, you should
just cook for your kids at home

854
00:49:23,370 --> 00:49:28,790
and just online shop
with your husband's money.

855
00:49:28,880 --> 00:49:32,380
Why the heck do these women
have to drive on the road

856
00:49:32,460 --> 00:49:36,260
and get in the way of a great man?

857
00:49:40,220 --> 00:49:42,510
I don't have a husband who makes money,

858
00:49:43,220 --> 00:49:45,680
but I still need to feed my kid.

859
00:49:46,390 --> 00:49:47,980
So I drive this smelly truck

860
00:49:48,060 --> 00:49:50,440
-to make money--
-Oh, I see.

861
00:49:50,520 --> 00:49:52,270
So you don't have a husband.

862
00:49:52,360 --> 00:49:53,190
Lady.

863
00:49:54,280 --> 00:49:58,030
I knew it as soon as I saw you.

864
00:49:58,700 --> 00:50:00,570
The way you talk back to me

865
00:50:00,660 --> 00:50:04,040
shows just how tough your life must be.

866
00:50:04,700 --> 00:50:05,580
My gosh.

867
00:50:05,660 --> 00:50:08,120
How could you be so brazen and yell at me?

868
00:50:08,670 --> 00:50:09,830
I can't believe this.

869
00:50:12,000 --> 00:50:13,210
Goodness.

870
00:50:13,300 --> 00:50:15,960
Goodness, look at you.

871
00:50:17,260 --> 00:50:20,140
I told her she didn't have to
worry about a thing.

872
00:50:21,090 --> 00:50:23,640
But look at him now. What do I do?

873
00:50:24,220 --> 00:50:25,430
Goodness.

874
00:50:27,810 --> 00:50:28,690
Darn it!

875
00:50:28,770 --> 00:50:31,810
Those darned twins.

876
00:50:32,560 --> 00:50:34,650
My gosh.

877
00:50:35,480 --> 00:50:36,530
Goodness.

878
00:50:37,690 --> 00:50:38,650
Wait.

879
00:50:39,740 --> 00:50:40,780
Shouldn't he

880
00:50:41,570 --> 00:50:43,410
wash his lower body too?

881
00:50:43,490 --> 00:50:45,040
Right.

882
00:50:45,620 --> 00:50:49,040
Just strip him naked and wash him.

883
00:50:49,120 --> 00:50:51,540
Just pretend he's a seven-year-old.

884
00:50:52,880 --> 00:50:55,300
But still, his body
isn't that of a seven-year-old.

885
00:50:55,380 --> 00:50:59,720
Then what do we do?
Do we just leave him covered up in mud?

886
00:50:59,800 --> 00:51:03,010
Then you do it. Think of him as Sam-sik.

887
00:51:03,680 --> 00:51:06,850
Why would I bathe that damned kid?

888
00:51:07,930 --> 00:51:10,190
Then I'll do it.

889
00:51:11,100 --> 00:51:13,810
I bathe my husband too.

890
00:51:13,900 --> 00:51:16,360
-Oh, my.
-Sparkling clean.

891
00:51:17,030 --> 00:51:19,240
He gets sulky and refuses to eat

892
00:51:19,320 --> 00:51:20,990
if I don't bathe him.

893
00:51:21,570 --> 00:51:23,620
He's such a whiny baby.

894
00:51:25,910 --> 00:51:27,660
All right. Here we go.

895
00:51:28,750 --> 00:51:29,700
Oh, my.

896
00:51:30,750 --> 00:51:33,580
-It's all right. I'll be gentle.
-Well…

897
00:51:34,380 --> 00:51:36,170
-Hey, she's back.
-Mom!

898
00:51:36,250 --> 00:51:37,500
Mom!

899
00:51:37,590 --> 00:51:38,510
Mom!

900
00:52:05,780 --> 00:52:06,620
Mom.

901
00:52:08,160 --> 00:52:10,910
May I go out for a moment?

902
00:52:14,920 --> 00:52:18,170
I lost Ye-jin's bouncy ball
while we were playing.

903
00:52:19,380 --> 00:52:20,510
No.

904
00:52:21,300 --> 00:52:22,300
We weren't playing.

905
00:52:22,380 --> 00:52:23,760
We were exercising.

906
00:52:23,840 --> 00:52:25,260
I studied too, Mom.

907
00:52:25,800 --> 00:52:28,470
Silverfish, cabbage caterpillars, fleas,

908
00:52:28,560 --> 00:52:30,770
and aphids live in a flower.

909
00:52:30,850 --> 00:52:33,270
This flower is actually
a napa cabbage flower.

910
00:52:34,350 --> 00:52:36,940
But I didn't know that.

911
00:52:41,940 --> 00:52:43,950
I have to find that bouncy ball.

912
00:52:47,240 --> 00:52:49,370
She's going to tell her dad.

913
00:52:49,450 --> 00:52:53,500
And their dad is a horrifying bastard,
so he's really scary.

914
00:52:54,040 --> 00:52:56,080
Mom, please, just once.

915
00:52:56,170 --> 00:52:58,460
It'll only be a moment. I'll be quick.

916
00:52:58,540 --> 00:53:00,960
Right, why don't we go together?

917
00:53:04,050 --> 00:53:05,800
Why did you live like that?

918
00:53:05,880 --> 00:53:07,510
Why did you live like that?

919
00:53:09,220 --> 00:53:10,100
What's all this?

920
00:53:11,010 --> 00:53:13,430
Did you take money and bribes
and do bad things?

921
00:53:14,310 --> 00:53:16,520
No, right? Say you didn't.

922
00:53:17,100 --> 00:53:18,360
Say you didn't!

923
00:53:18,440 --> 00:53:20,730
Say you didn't!

924
00:53:24,610 --> 00:53:26,450
You brought tears and pain

925
00:53:27,160 --> 00:53:28,990
into other people's lives!

926
00:53:30,080 --> 00:53:31,910
Did you think you'd live a good life?

927
00:53:33,040 --> 00:53:34,910
Did you think you'd be fine?

928
00:53:36,580 --> 00:53:37,460
Look.

929
00:53:38,460 --> 00:53:41,540
Look how you've been punished
for what you've done!

930
00:53:41,630 --> 00:53:42,920
Look!

931
00:53:43,840 --> 00:53:45,220
Look, you punk.

932
00:53:59,810 --> 00:54:01,310
It's all my fault.

933
00:54:02,940 --> 00:54:06,190
I told you to help those in need.

934
00:54:07,280 --> 00:54:10,200
I told you to save
those who have been wronged.

935
00:54:10,990 --> 00:54:13,450
But I ended up raising you like this.

936
00:54:15,870 --> 00:54:19,460
I locked you up in a pigsty
and didn't even let you breathe,

937
00:54:19,540 --> 00:54:21,630
telling you to only study!

938
00:54:30,390 --> 00:54:33,470
I wanted to make you rich and powerful,

939
00:54:34,430 --> 00:54:38,350
but instead, I made you
into a cold-hearted monster!

940
00:54:43,400 --> 00:54:44,610
It's my fault.

941
00:54:45,230 --> 00:54:48,070
-It's my fault!
-Mom.

942
00:54:49,820 --> 00:54:52,910
Mom.

943
00:54:52,990 --> 00:54:55,490
Mom, I'm sorry.

944
00:54:55,580 --> 00:54:58,040
Mom, I was wrong. I won't do that again.

945
00:55:00,120 --> 00:55:01,170
Mom…

946
00:55:03,790 --> 00:55:07,510
But I really don't remember, Mom.

947
00:55:10,930 --> 00:55:14,720
Am I a bad person, Mom?

948
00:55:16,350 --> 00:55:17,970
Is that why I was punished?

949
00:55:19,020 --> 00:55:21,140
Was this a punishment from above

950
00:55:22,150 --> 00:55:24,060
and not a chance?

951
00:55:25,610 --> 00:55:27,980
No.

952
00:55:29,070 --> 00:55:30,070
No.

953
00:55:31,030 --> 00:55:32,030
No.

954
00:55:33,200 --> 00:55:34,200
Mom.

955
00:55:36,240 --> 00:55:38,200
Mom, I'm sorry.

956
00:55:38,830 --> 00:55:39,830
No.

957
00:55:41,330 --> 00:55:42,330
No.

958
00:55:52,930 --> 00:55:53,930
All done.

959
00:55:55,300 --> 00:55:56,140
Come over here.

960
00:55:57,260 --> 00:55:58,260
It stinks.

961
00:56:00,730 --> 00:56:01,810
You're right.

962
00:56:02,980 --> 00:56:06,270
That's why you hated this place so much.

963
00:56:07,020 --> 00:56:10,490
And I also didn't want to bring you

964
00:56:11,150 --> 00:56:12,780
to such a smelly, dirty place.

965
00:56:15,530 --> 00:56:16,530
But…

966
00:56:19,290 --> 00:56:21,870
there's something
I really want to show you now.

967
00:56:30,630 --> 00:56:35,300
There are two animals
that are useful from their head to toe.

968
00:56:35,970 --> 00:56:37,350
Do you know what they are?

969
00:56:39,350 --> 00:56:40,430
Humans…

970
00:56:41,680 --> 00:56:42,770
and pigs.

971
00:56:44,270 --> 00:56:48,520
Everyone thinks pigs are dirty and smelly,

972
00:56:48,610 --> 00:56:50,020
but that's not the case.

973
00:56:50,860 --> 00:56:54,110
They not only
do their business in one place,

974
00:56:54,200 --> 00:56:55,820
but they also only sleep where it's clean.

975
00:56:57,450 --> 00:56:59,870
They bathe often in mud to cool themselves

976
00:56:59,950 --> 00:57:01,830
and get rid of bugs.

977
00:57:03,040 --> 00:57:04,540
But humans

978
00:57:04,620 --> 00:57:08,250
started to lock them up in tiny pigsties.

979
00:57:10,630 --> 00:57:13,840
The pigs couldn't bathe in mud anymore,

980
00:57:13,920 --> 00:57:17,260
so they began to rub their bodies
on their own excrement.

981
00:57:18,260 --> 00:57:21,970
That's how they grew dirtier
and more aggressive.

982
00:57:25,060 --> 00:57:26,390
Isn't that so sad?

983
00:57:27,560 --> 00:57:28,610
It is.

984
00:57:29,940 --> 00:57:31,900
However, what's really sad is this.

985
00:57:32,900 --> 00:57:34,900
Pigs are unable to lift their heads,

986
00:57:34,990 --> 00:57:37,610
so they live their entire life
staring at the ground.

987
00:57:38,740 --> 00:57:43,200
There is only one way for a pig
to look up at the sky.

988
00:57:45,460 --> 00:57:46,620
It's…

989
00:57:47,500 --> 00:57:48,880
to fall down.

990
00:57:50,710 --> 00:57:52,000
Fall down?

991
00:57:52,090 --> 00:57:52,920
Yes.

992
00:57:53,000 --> 00:57:54,260
That's right.

993
00:57:55,170 --> 00:57:56,840
Falling down

994
00:57:56,930 --> 00:58:00,300
is a way for you to see another world,
a world you have never seen before,

995
00:58:01,850 --> 00:58:02,970
both for pigs

996
00:58:03,970 --> 00:58:05,180
and people.

997
00:58:15,110 --> 00:58:17,990
We have fallen over right now.

998
00:58:18,660 --> 00:58:20,820
Both Mom and you, Kang-ho.

999
00:58:21,870 --> 00:58:24,120
That's how we got to see this new world.

1000
00:58:25,370 --> 00:58:28,540
A world we've never seen
and we couldn't see before.

1001
00:58:29,830 --> 00:58:31,710
A precious world

1002
00:58:32,840 --> 00:58:34,750
that we were meant to see.

1003
00:58:37,090 --> 00:58:38,680
A precious world.

1004
00:58:54,360 --> 00:58:55,400
I'm sorry.

1005
00:58:57,530 --> 00:58:58,860
-Hello?
-Hey!

1006
00:58:59,450 --> 00:59:00,860
Where are you?

1007
00:59:00,950 --> 00:59:02,820
When will you pay me back…

1008
00:59:04,370 --> 00:59:06,830
I'm sorry. Goodness.

1009
00:59:09,250 --> 00:59:10,790
Is this it?

1010
00:59:10,870 --> 00:59:12,880
-I'm sure of it.
-It's here.

1011
00:59:15,130 --> 00:59:16,090
Excuse me.

1012
00:59:16,170 --> 00:59:18,050
Lee Mi-joo is here, right? Where is she?

1013
00:59:18,130 --> 00:59:20,800
-Where's Lee Mi-joo?
-What are you doing?

1014
00:59:20,880 --> 00:59:21,880
Are you the owner?

1015
00:59:21,970 --> 00:59:24,600
-Yes. What's the matter?
-Where's Lee Mi-joo?

1016
00:59:24,680 --> 00:59:26,600
That bitch ran off
with our membership fees.

1017
00:59:26,680 --> 00:59:29,890
And that bitch Baek Sun-young
took two million won from me!

1018
00:59:29,980 --> 00:59:32,020
She's not here, so please leave.

1019
00:59:32,100 --> 00:59:33,650
-Leave.
-Call the police!

1020
00:59:33,730 --> 00:59:35,190
-Look around!
-Okay.

1021
00:59:35,270 --> 00:59:36,610
-Stop this.
-I'm not leaving!

1022
00:59:36,690 --> 00:59:37,900
-Start looking!
-Stop it!

1023
00:59:37,980 --> 00:59:39,320
-Stop it!
-Move aside!

1024
00:59:39,400 --> 00:59:40,820
-Move!
-Hey!

1025
00:59:41,570 --> 00:59:42,530
There she is.

1026
00:59:42,610 --> 00:59:43,740
It's her.

1027
00:59:43,820 --> 00:59:45,450
Please give me some more time.

1028
00:59:45,950 --> 00:59:47,990
I'll pay you back soon.

1029
00:59:49,620 --> 00:59:52,710
So Mi-joo, are you drinking soju?

1030
00:59:53,210 --> 00:59:55,210
It's too early to be drinking.

1031
00:59:55,290 --> 00:59:57,050
You must not know.

1032
00:59:57,130 --> 01:00:00,130
Soju tastes best after you get fired.

1033
01:00:00,210 --> 01:00:01,550
Right.

1034
01:00:02,300 --> 01:00:03,930
I got fired again.

1035
01:00:04,010 --> 01:00:06,640
I got fired because I was too old.

1036
01:00:06,720 --> 01:00:08,850
I got fired because of my bad credit.

1037
01:00:08,930 --> 01:00:11,100
I got fired because of my creditors.

1038
01:00:16,980 --> 01:00:19,400
Should I just go back to my kids
and start farming?

1039
01:00:19,480 --> 01:00:20,940
Do you think farming's a joke?

1040
01:00:21,570 --> 01:00:23,530
Do you know how hard it is?

1041
01:00:23,610 --> 01:00:26,570
Do you know what the adequate distance
between rice plants is?

1042
01:00:27,330 --> 01:00:28,790
When do you spray sterilizers,

1043
01:00:28,870 --> 01:00:30,950
pesticides, and nutrients for peppers?

1044
01:00:31,540 --> 01:00:33,250
Why don't you

1045
01:00:33,330 --> 01:00:35,080
just go to the US with me?

1046
01:00:36,000 --> 01:00:38,500
Let's go find Sun-young

1047
01:00:38,590 --> 01:00:41,260
and that asshole who abandoned you
and left for the US.

1048
01:00:42,260 --> 01:00:45,390
You should find him and get alimony.

1049
01:00:45,470 --> 01:00:46,640
What do you say?

1050
01:00:47,350 --> 01:00:48,890
Do you think we can get a visa?

1051
01:00:49,810 --> 01:00:53,390
I have bad credit,
and you're an ex-convict.

1052
01:00:53,480 --> 01:00:54,890
You're smart.

1053
01:00:59,440 --> 01:01:02,490
How are you?
How's working on a fishing vessel?

1054
01:01:03,190 --> 01:01:04,200
Where are you?

1055
01:01:05,490 --> 01:01:06,450
Me?

1056
01:01:07,370 --> 01:01:11,490
I'm, well, somewhere in the Pacific.

1057
01:01:12,120 --> 01:01:15,040
Goodness, look at the dolphins jumping.

1058
01:01:19,210 --> 01:01:21,420
Can you hear the dolphins?

1059
01:01:21,500 --> 01:01:22,670
Yes.

1060
01:01:22,760 --> 01:01:25,340
You're far away,
but you have great reception.

1061
01:01:25,430 --> 01:01:27,720
It's because my heart
is always by your side.

1062
01:01:32,470 --> 01:01:35,440
Anyway, I'm glad
you got your act together.

1063
01:01:35,520 --> 01:01:37,310
Do you know why I did that?

1064
01:01:38,060 --> 01:01:39,230
Just hang in there.

1065
01:01:39,310 --> 01:01:40,730
I'll earn a lot of money

1066
01:01:40,820 --> 01:01:43,150
and pay off all of your debt.

1067
01:01:44,690 --> 01:01:46,740
But until then,

1068
01:01:46,820 --> 01:01:49,910
please remain the Lee Mi-joo
I've always known.

1069
01:01:49,990 --> 01:01:53,540
The Mi-joo who never loses to anybody,

1070
01:01:53,620 --> 01:01:56,370
whether it be to a boy,
your dad, or your sisters.

1071
01:01:58,880 --> 01:02:00,750
Thanks, Sam-sik.

1072
01:02:01,340 --> 01:02:02,710
Take care.

1073
01:02:02,800 --> 01:02:03,880
Okay.

1074
01:02:04,550 --> 01:02:05,720
I'll call you again.

1075
01:02:05,800 --> 01:02:06,880
Bye.

1076
01:02:09,340 --> 01:02:10,850
FISHING UNION
COMMUNAL WORKSHOP

1077
01:02:10,930 --> 01:02:14,220
Let me know if you need anything.

1078
01:02:14,310 --> 01:02:15,930
-Hurry.
-I need beer.

1079
01:02:16,020 --> 01:02:17,560
Sure, coming.

1080
01:02:18,810 --> 01:02:20,100
Two large beers.

1081
01:02:20,190 --> 01:02:22,610
-A pack of cigarettes.
-Cigarettes.

1082
01:02:24,820 --> 01:02:26,150
Blow.

1083
01:02:27,610 --> 01:02:28,820
How gross.

1084
01:02:28,910 --> 01:02:29,910
Mom.

1085
01:02:35,200 --> 01:02:36,080
Mom.

1086
01:02:36,620 --> 01:02:37,540
Mom.

1087
01:02:41,000 --> 01:02:43,170
I'm going to go feed the pigs.

1088
01:02:43,250 --> 01:02:45,670
Have some snacks and watch TV, okay?

1089
01:02:46,800 --> 01:02:48,380
And if anything happens…

1090
01:02:49,050 --> 01:02:50,300
"Remember to call, okay?"

1091
01:02:51,260 --> 01:02:52,090
Yes.

1092
01:02:52,180 --> 01:02:53,600
I'll be quick.

1093
01:03:11,450 --> 01:03:13,990
She didn't say I couldn't go out.

1094
01:03:16,200 --> 01:03:17,290
Right?

1095
01:03:25,960 --> 01:03:27,420
What do you mean, plagiarized?

1096
01:03:27,510 --> 01:03:31,470
Similar lyrics isn't plagiarism.

1097
01:03:32,090 --> 01:03:33,140
Hey, look.

1098
01:03:33,220 --> 01:03:35,640
What Na Hoon-a's mother loved
was ripe persimmon,

1099
01:03:35,720 --> 01:03:38,850
but what my mother loved
was firm persimmon.

1100
01:03:38,930 --> 01:03:40,020
Listen to this.

1101
01:03:40,690 --> 01:03:43,230
Gingers grow

1102
01:03:43,310 --> 01:03:46,110
Na Hoon-a sang about thinking,
but I'm singing about ginger.

1103
01:03:46,690 --> 01:03:49,320
When firm persimmons grow

1104
01:03:49,400 --> 01:03:50,400
Hello?

1105
01:03:51,610 --> 01:03:52,450
Damn it!

1106
01:04:00,790 --> 01:04:02,500
What is that?

1107
01:04:04,920 --> 01:04:06,420
Hey.

1108
01:04:07,460 --> 01:04:08,460
Who are you?

1109
01:04:09,260 --> 01:04:11,260
Hello. I'm Choi Kang-ho.

1110
01:04:11,340 --> 01:04:13,220
What is Choi Kang-ho doing here?

1111
01:04:13,840 --> 01:04:15,470
Right, well…

1112
01:04:16,010 --> 01:04:17,890
I'm looking for Ye-jin's bouncy ball.

1113
01:04:18,430 --> 01:04:19,520
Have you seen it?

1114
01:04:19,600 --> 01:04:20,430
It's pink…

1115
01:04:23,020 --> 01:04:24,020
and it's this big.

1116
01:04:24,810 --> 01:04:26,360
This is so ridiculous.

1117
01:04:27,110 --> 01:04:29,230
This is intrusion upon habitation.

1118
01:04:30,070 --> 01:04:32,070
Leave before I report you!

1119
01:04:32,150 --> 01:04:34,780
"Criminal Act, Article 319,
Intrusion upon Habitation."

1120
01:04:34,860 --> 01:04:37,660
"A person who intrudes upon
one’s residence, guarded building,

1121
01:04:37,740 --> 01:04:40,080
structure, ship, or occupied room,
shall be punished

1122
01:04:40,160 --> 01:04:43,120
for up to three years
or by a fine under five million won."

1123
01:04:46,330 --> 01:04:48,130
But what is an intrusion upon habitation?

1124
01:04:51,920 --> 01:04:54,050
You're just a village idiot, aren't you?

1125
01:04:54,130 --> 01:04:55,220
Get out of here!

1126
01:05:01,810 --> 01:05:04,020
Goodbye, then!

1127
01:05:08,610 --> 01:05:09,820
But you know,

1128
01:05:10,480 --> 01:05:11,820
I'm not an idiot.

1129
01:05:12,610 --> 01:05:14,320
I just returned to my childhood.

1130
01:05:14,990 --> 01:05:17,370
This is a chance given from above.

1131
01:05:17,450 --> 01:05:19,160
I'll also give you a chance.

1132
01:05:19,240 --> 01:05:21,080
You get three seconds

1133
01:05:21,830 --> 01:05:23,000
to get lost!

1134
01:05:23,540 --> 01:05:24,620
One.

1135
01:05:25,750 --> 01:05:26,670
Two.

1136
01:05:27,960 --> 01:05:30,000
Wait, darn it.

1137
01:05:30,500 --> 01:05:32,800
Three! I challenge you to a duel!

1138
01:05:37,050 --> 01:05:38,180
Where did he…

1139
01:05:39,350 --> 01:05:40,600
Did he fall?

1140
01:05:46,230 --> 01:05:47,560
Hi, Kang-ho.

1141
01:05:48,190 --> 01:05:49,650
Are you looking for something?

1142
01:06:51,960 --> 01:06:53,170
Kang-ho!

1143
01:07:21,610 --> 01:07:22,530
Kang-ho!

1144
01:07:22,620 --> 01:07:23,910
Kang-ho!

1145
01:07:53,810 --> 01:07:57,860
I LIKE YOU VERY MUCH.

1146
01:08:27,010 --> 01:08:28,220
Choi Kang-ho!

1147
01:08:53,330 --> 01:08:54,670
I'm dead.

1148
01:09:05,840 --> 01:09:06,890
Found it.

1149
01:09:08,890 --> 01:09:10,680
I found it!

1150
01:09:13,180 --> 01:09:16,020
Ye-jin, Seo-jin! I found it!

1151
01:09:16,100 --> 01:09:17,150
I found it!

1152
01:09:28,450 --> 01:09:30,330
One, two, three.

1153
01:09:31,740 --> 01:09:32,790
I found it.

1154
01:09:34,370 --> 01:09:37,080
I can do it. I can take it down.

1155
01:09:47,640 --> 01:09:50,100
Ye-jin! Seo-jin!

1156
01:09:59,900 --> 01:10:01,400
Ye-jin! Seo-jin!

1157
01:10:03,440 --> 01:10:05,740
Ye-jin! Seo-jin!

1158
01:10:10,780 --> 01:10:12,160
Who is it?

1159
01:10:37,390 --> 01:10:40,310
THE GOOD BAD MOTHER

1160
01:10:55,450 --> 01:10:57,040
Someone I don't know.

1161
01:10:57,790 --> 01:10:59,540
But it hurts right here.

1162
01:10:59,620 --> 01:11:00,620
And it's something…

1163
01:11:01,210 --> 01:11:02,880
you need to do on your own.

1164
01:11:04,340 --> 01:11:07,130
If you ever get in my way,

1165
01:11:07,210 --> 01:11:08,590
I will not condone it.

1166
01:11:08,670 --> 01:11:11,590
I rotted in prison for months
because of you!

1167
01:11:11,680 --> 01:11:14,430
Violation of Article 49, Paragraph 1,
Item 10 of the Road Traffic Act.

1168
01:11:15,010 --> 01:11:17,100
-He was never my friend.
-Mi-joo?

1169
01:11:18,890 --> 01:11:20,020
Mi-joo.

1170
01:11:20,100 --> 01:11:21,190
Do you remember her?

1171
01:11:21,270 --> 01:11:23,860
Seeing how you came back
with all your stuff,

1172
01:11:23,940 --> 01:11:26,400
it looks like you've come to stay.

1173
01:11:26,480 --> 01:11:29,700
I know it wasn't easy for you to come.
Let's live together.

1174
01:11:29,780 --> 01:11:30,650
Don't call him.

1175
01:11:30,740 --> 01:11:33,700
Don't ever meet him
or play with him again.

1176
